  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `erigon version 2022.07.4-alpha-d88fc824`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 22.04\r\n\r\nCommit hash : d88fc8242\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n`eth_blockNumber` returning the last valid block. \r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n`eth_blockNumber` returns a different block.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nTry to sync up sepolia testnet with erigon + teku or erigon + nimbus (it is possible that other clients also don't work, these are just the two I have tested so far). \r\n\r\nAPI call `eth_syncing` returns the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\nGeth + teku:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":false}\r\n\r\nErigon + nimbus:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":false}\r\n\r\nBesu + prysm:\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\" : \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\" : 1,\r\n  \"result\" : false\r\n}\r\nNethermind + lighthouse:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"result\":false,\"id\":1}\r\nGeth2 + lodestar :\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":false}\r\n\r\nErigon2 + teku:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":false}\r\n```\r\nTherefore, I assume that the chain is fully synced, however when I run the API call `eth_blockNumber` I get the following\r\n\r\n```\r\nGeth + teku:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x18687f\"}\r\n\r\nErigon + nimbus:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x184e2c\"}\r\n\r\nBesu + prysm:\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\" : \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\" : 1,\r\n  \"result\" : \"0x18687f\"\r\n}\r\nNethermind + lighthouse:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"result\":\"0x18687f\",\"id\":1}\r\nGeth2 + lodestar:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x18687f\"}\r\n\r\nErigon2 + teku:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x17f157\"}\r\n```\r\nThe correct block is indeed `0x18687f` and not `0x184e2c` or `0x17f157` that are produced by the clients with erigon EL clients. \r\n\r\nAlso teku reports an error when connected to erigon:\r\n\r\n```\r\nERROR - PLEASE FIX OR REPORT | Unexpected exception thrown for forkchoice-async-0 java.util.concurrent.CompletionException: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Cannot change node validity from VALID to INVALID (See log file for full stack trace)\r\n```\r\n\r\nSimilarly the API endpoints of the CLs report inconsistent finalized roots:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTeku + geth\r\n{\"execution_optimistic\":false,\"data\":{\"root\":\"0xe47f5122d6bc2e84919eac99dbf3cc2bddf9ad9b42ec30f1faa1c9b0c2416f03\"}}\r\nNimbus + erigon\r\n{\"execution_optimistic\":false,\"data\":{\"root\":\"0x0997b6522ec31a0c22acb28f9e5c136e4666ca77807a9310e18908443ce2383a\"}}\r\nPrysm + besu\r\n{\"data\":{\"root\":\"0xe47f5122d6bc2e84919eac99dbf3cc2bddf9ad9b42ec30f1faa1c9b0c2416f03\"},\"execution_optimistic\":false}\r\nLighthouse + nethermind\r\n{\"data\":{\"root\":\"0xe47f5122d6bc2e84919eac99dbf3cc2bddf9ad9b42ec30f1faa1c9b0c2416f03\"}}\r\nLodestar + geth2\r\n{\"data\":\"0xe47f5122d6bc2e84919eac99dbf3cc2bddf9ad9b42ec30f1faa1c9b0c2416f03\"}\r\nTeku2 + erigon2\r\n{\"execution_optimistic\":false,\"data\":{\"root\":\"0x1ec1c2fc2aac407e0dffd9fef29fcea486d0d041d07e5e57eaa643505906223a\"}}\r\nNimbus2 + geth3\r\n{\"execution_optimistic\":false,\"data\":{\"root\":\"0xe47f5122d6bc2e84919eac99dbf3cc2bddf9ad9b42ec30f1faa1c9b0c2416f03\"}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe only common denominator between them is erigon. So I assume there might be something broken in the latest release. \r\n",
